\paragraph{Status note (Phase C1, post-refactor).}
Following the Phase~C1 refactor (iter-109), the Lean body of \texttt{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.LineBundle} matches the geometric definition stated above. Concretely,
\[
  \mathrm{LineBundle}\,X \;:=\; \bigl(\mathrm{Skeleton}\,X.\mathrm{Modules}\bigr)^{\!\times},
\]
the units of the (commutative) monoid structure on the skeleton of the symmetric monoidal category $X.\mathrm{Modules}$ (Theorem~\ref{thm:Modules_MonoidalCategory}). This mirrors the ring-side precedent $\mathrm{CommRing.Pic}\,R = \mathrm{Shrink}\bigl(\mathrm{Skeleton}\,(\mathrm{SemimoduleCat}\,R)\bigr)^{\!\times}$ at \texttt{Mathlib.RingTheory.PicardGroup:407}; the commutative-group structure derives from $\mathrm{Skeleton.instCommMonoid}$ (\texttt{Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Monoidal.Skeleton:80}) followed by $\mathrm{instCommGroupUnits}$. No \texttt{Shrink} wrapper is needed: $X.\mathrm{Modules}$ already lives in $\mathrm{Type}\,(u+1)$, so $\mathrm{LineBundle}\,X$ inhabits the same universe and the downstream \texttt{PicardFunctor}/\texttt{PicardFunctorAb} codomains have been bumped to match.

\paragraph{Load-bearing transitive dependency on \texorpdfstring{$W.\mathrm{IsMonoidal}$}{W.IsMonoidal}.}
The $\mathrm{BraidedCategory}\,(X.\mathrm{Modules})$ instance underlying the commutative-group structure is supplied by $\mathrm{Localization.Monoidal.Braided}$ (\texttt{Mathlib.CategoryTheory.Localization.Monoidal.Braided:118}), which requires $W(X).\mathrm{IsMonoidal}$ for the sheafification class $W(X)$. This is the project's named-deferred sorry $\mathrm{instIsMonoidal\_W}$ (\texttt{AlgebraicJacobian/Modules/Monoidal.lean:166}); see the load-bearing-disclosure paragraph in Chapter~\ref{chap:Modules_Monoidal}. Post-C1, every theorem about $\mathrm{LineBundle}\,X$, $\Pic(X)$, $\mathrm{Pic.pullback}$, $\mathrm{PicardFunctor}$, $\mathrm{PicardFunctorAb}$, and the downstream Jacobian arc transitively consumes $\mathrm{instIsMonoidal\_W}$; \texttt{lean\_verify} surfaces \texttt{sorryAx} in their axiom chains.

\paragraph{Pull-back gap.}
Theorem~\ref{thm:Scheme_Pic_pullback} below (and the associated functoriality lemmas $\mathrm{Pic.pullback\_id}$, $\mathrm{Pic.pullback\_comp}$) is currently sorry-bodied. The obstruction is a separate named-deferred Mathlib gap, recorded as Theorem~\ref{thm:SheafOfModules_pullback_tensorObj} below, asserting that the categorical pull-back functor $\mathrm{Scheme.Modules.pullback}\,f$ is monoidal. The named-deferral route is chosen per analogist option~(c) of \texttt{analogies/c1-route.md}; see also the Phase~C1 row of \texttt{STRATEGY.md}.

